featured_reviews.review_id:
The Kattu Thaikka Aroosiya Mosque (kaattttut taikkaa aruusiyyaa plllli) , one of the most well-known mosques in Kayalpatnam, was constructed in the 1953 and restored in 2012.

Muslims can visit this mosque to participate in the five daily prayers that are required of them. There are separate prayer rooms for men and women. It has a marble floor, is air-conditioned, cool, and historical.

During the month of Ramadan, there is a place set aside on the first floor of the mosque for ladies to give special night prayers, and the area is tidy and organised.

Throughout the whole month of Ramadan, Kanji (porridge) was served to every member of the neighbourhood.
